history.content:
The 2015-16 draft schedule is our best understanding of what is possible at this time. It is highly unlikely that 168 will be able to be re-added to the Spring 16 schedule.

The 2016-17 draft schedule will be available sometime between late December and early March.

CS 168 and EE 122 are generally offered in alternate semesters and cover much of the same material.

EE 122 is being taught in the spring.

children.subject:
The class website says what you wrote, and is probably more reliable.

But the course catalog says 61B and 162, which is what I assume the poster was referring to.
Where does it say 162 is a prereq for 168? I only see CS 61A, 61B, Math 53 or 54?

history.content:
I remember that on the EECS website, it was listed last semester that CS 168 would be offered next Spring (and taught by Professor Randy Katz, if I remember correctly). However, I checked the website again recently, and found that it is no longer going to be offered in Spring 2016.

I decided not to take CS 168 this semester because CS 162 is a prerequisite, and I wanted to take that first. So my plan was to take CS 162 this semester and CS 168 next semester. However, I didn't anticipate that CS 168 would be cancelled in Spring 2016, and I am a bit surprised it's being cancelled because CS 168 seems to be a popular course this semester (Fall 2015).

I really want to take this course since Computer Networks are of interest to me and taking CS 168 would help me with the research I am doing as part of the AmpLab. Is there any chance that CS 168 will be offered in Spring of 2016? If not, when will the course next be offered?
history.subject: CS 168 in Spring 2016
